The paper deals with a geometric graph problem of constructing a spanner for a directed transmission graph, which is a graph with vertices representing points in the plane with associated radii. This problem involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS) to efficiently compute the spanner. The paper also discusses applications of the spanner in network algorithms (cs.NA) and graph theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the problem involves analyzing the structure of the transmission graph, which can be related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
